            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Mateo Malhotra\u2019s name is a story in itself, a constant icebreaker he\u2019s been navigating his entire life. Raised in Fremont by his Indian father, a first-generation software architect, and his white American mother, a pragmatic high school science teacher, Mateo grew up in a household that valued both analytical thinking and practical application. While he inherited his father\u2019s surname and love for systems, he took after his mother\u2019s fair Irish features, leading him to identify as white, a label that felt most aligned with how the world perceived him.\n\nHis childhood was a comfortable blend of suburban quiet and intellectual curiosity. While his father hoped he\u2019d follow him into coding, Mateo was always more interested in the physical world\u2014how assembly lines worked, why traffic flowed in specific patterns, and how to make things *better*. This passion led him to Cal Poly\u2019s acclaimed Industrial Engineering program. A pivotal moment came during a summer internship where he redesigned a warehouse layout, saving the company thousands in operational costs. The thrill of seeing his abstract plans create tangible efficiency solidified his career path. He immediately pursued a Master's degree, eager to get a competitive edge.\n\nNow 24, Mateo is a Process Engineer for a medical device manufacturer in South San Francisco. He lives in a shared three-bedroom apartment in the Mission District, a vibrant neighborhood whose energy he thrives on. His daily routine is quintessentially SF: a morning jog past Dolores Park, a quick coffee from a local cafe, and a 40-minute BART ride south, podcast playing in his ears. The $110,000 salary affords him a comfortable life, but he\u2019s still budget-conscious, preferring trivia nights with work friends and exploring the city\u2019s endless taquerias over expensive clubs.\n\nHis connection to San Francisco is one of professional and personal ambition. He sees the city as an epicenter of innovation where his skills are highly valued. Mateo\u2019s dream isn\u2019t just to climb the corporate ladder, but to eventually apply his optimization expertise to humanitarian logistics or sustainable manufacturing. For now, he\u2019s focused on proving himself, building his social circle, and enjoying the chaotic, brilliant, and demanding life of a young professional in a city that constantly asks for your best."
